.git
.env
docs
eval
tests
output
models
README.md
**/__pycache__
.DS_Store

# SFT data must never enter the build context. .gitignore alone is not enough —
# docker sends the whole context to the daemon, and one careless `COPY . .`
# would bake a competitive asset into a PUBLIC image.
finetune/
llama.cpp/
*.jsonl
.env
eval/
# ...but the fine-tuned WEIGHTS are the product and must be COPY-able. The
# image is public anyway (the grader pulls it), so this exposes nothing the
# GGUF inside the image doesn't already.
!finetune/out/general.gguf
# ...and the code-exemplar retrieval bundle ships in the image too.
!finetune/rag/codebundle
!finetune/rag/codebundle/**
